          "id": "m8s1",
          "title": "8.1 What are Large Language Models",
          "brief": "<h4>What are Large Language Models</h4><ul><li>LLMs: neural networks trained on massive text data</li><li>Transformer architecture with attention mechanism</li><li>GPT-4, Gemini, Claude, LLaMA — key models</li><li>Capabilities: text generation, code writing, reasoning</li><li>For DBAs: natural language to SQL, documentation, troubleshooting</li><li>Limitations: hallucination, context windows, cost</li></ul>",
          "description": "<p><strong>Large Language Models are the foundation of modern AI assistants and can transform DBA workflows.</strong></p>",
          "syntax": "# LLM interaction pattern\nimport openai\n\nclient = openai.OpenAI(api_key='...')\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model='gpt-4',\n    messages=[\n        {'role': 'system', 'content': 'You are a SQL Server DBA expert.'},\n        {'role': 'user', 'content': 'How do I fix error 9002?'}\n    ]\n)\nprint(response.choices[0].message.content)",
          "script": "Introduce LLMs and their relevance to DBAs.\nExplain transformer architecture simply.\nShow practical DBA applications.",
          "examples": [
            {
              "name": "Parse Error Log",
              "code": "# Simulating SQL Server error log parsing\n# In production: open(r\"C:\\Program Files\\...\\ERRORLOG\")\n\nerror_log = \"\"\"2024-06-15 02:00:01.23 spid5s      Starting up database 'master'.\n2024-06-15 02:00:02.45 spid5s      Starting up database 'tempdb'.\n2024-06-15 08:15:33.12 spid55      Error: 1205, Severity: 13, State: 51.\n2024-06-15 08:15:33.12 spid55      Transaction was deadlocked on lock resources.\n2024-06-15 10:22:01.89 spid62      I/O request taking longer than 15 seconds.\n2024-06-15 10:22:01.89 spid62      Path: E:\\Data\\Sales.mdf\n2024-06-15 14:05:44.56 Logon       Login failed for user 'DOMAIN\\\\svc_old'. Reason: Password expired.\n2024-06-15 14:30:12.00 spid78      Error: 823, Severity: 24, State: 2.\n2024-06-15 14:30:12.00 spid78      Fatal error: I/O error (bad page) detected during read.\n\"\"\".strip().split(\"\\n\")\n\n# Parse and categorize\nerrors = []\nwarnings = []\nfor line in error_log:\n    if \"Error:\" in line:\n        # Extract severity\n        parts = line.split(\"Severity: \")\n        if len(parts) > 1:\n            severity = int(parts[1].split(\",\")[0])\n            errors.append({\"line\": line, \"severity\": severity})\n    elif \"I/O request taking\" in line or \"Login failed\" in line:\n        warnings.append(line)\n\nprint(f\"Error Log Analysis ({len(error_log)} lines):\")\nprint(f\"  Errors found:   {len(errors)}\")\nprint(f\"  Warnings found: {len(warnings)}\")\nprint()\nprint(\"Critical Errors (Severity >= 20):\")\nfor e in errors:\n    if e['severity'] >= 20:\n        print(f\"  \\u2622 Sev {e['severity']}: {e['line'][:70]}...\")\nprint()\nprint(\"Warnings:\")\nfor w in warnings:\n    print(f\"  \\u26a0 {w[:70]}...\")"
            },
            {
              "name": "Config Parser",
              "code": "# Parsing a DBA configuration file\nconfig_text = \"\"\"[monitoring]\ncheck_interval = 60\ncpu_threshold = 85\nmemory_threshold = 90\ndisk_threshold = 80\n\n[backup]\nfull_schedule = 02:00\nlog_interval_min = 15\nretention_days = 14\ncompression = true\n\n[alerting]\nemail_to = dba-team@company.com\nsms_critical = true\nteams_webhook = https://hooks.teams.com/abc123\n\"\"\"\n\n# Parse INI-style config\nconfig = {}\ncurrent_section = None\nfor line in config_text.strip().split(\"\\n\"):\n    line = line.strip()\n    if not line or line.startswith(\"#\"):\n        continue\n    if line.startswith(\"[\") and line.endswith(\"]\"):\n        current_section = line[1:-1]\n        config[current_section] = {}\n    elif \"=\" in line and current_section:\n        key, value = line.split(\"=\", 1)\n        config[current_section][key.strip()] = value.strip()\n\nprint(\"Parsed DBA Configuration:\")\nprint(\"=\" * 40)\nfor section, values in config.items():\n    print(f\"\\n[{section}]\")\n    for key, val in values.items():\n        print(f\"  {key:<20} = {val}\")\n\n# Use config values\ncpu_thresh = int(config['monitoring']['cpu_threshold'])\nprint(f\"\\nActive CPU threshold: {cpu_thresh}%\")"
            }
          ]
